579
00:30:06,980 --> 00:30:08,740
Said the procedure
went very well.

580
00:30:08,750 --> 00:30:10,580
Oh, good,
I've been meaning to...

581
00:30:10,580 --> 00:30:11,650
I...

582
00:30:12,210 --> 00:30:13,380
I wanted to tell you,

583
00:30:13,380 --> 00:30:15,280
and I want you
to hear from me first...

584
00:30:15,290 --> 00:30:17,290
there's an article about me

585
00:30:17,290 --> 00:30:19,920
coming out
in <i>The Times</i> tomorrow.

586
00:30:21,060 --> 00:30:22,790
It's not flattering.

587
00:30:24,090 --> 00:30:25,630
<font color="#138ce9">HARRY:</font> <font color="#ff00ff">(ON TV)</font> <i>Running? Me?</i>

588
00:30:25,630 --> 00:30:27,590
<i>Now, you know me
better than that.</i>

589
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:29,460
<font color="#138ce9">MARY:</font> <i>Three days and three
nights and not a word.</i>

590
00:30:29,470 --> 00:30:30,630
<font color="#138ce9">HARRY:</font> <i>Well, I've been very busy.</i>

591
00:30:30,630 --> 00:30:31,900
<font color="#138ce9">MARY:</font> <i>For all I knew
you were lying</i>

592
00:30:31,900 --> 00:30:33,000
<i>in the gutter somewhere...</i>

593
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:34,440
<i>with a knife in your back.</i>

594
00:30:34,440 --> 00:30:36,000
<font color="#138ce9">HARRY:</font> <i>Lying in the gutter?</i>

595
00:30:36,010 --> 00:30:37,270
<font color="#ff00ff">(PHONE RINGS)</font>

596
00:30:37,270 --> 00:30:39,580
<i>Now, look, sweetheart,
I'll tell you what happened.</i>

597
00:30:40,380 --> 00:30:42,240
- <i>I was in Birmingham.</i>
- <font color="#ff00ff">(BEN SIGHS)</font>

598
00:30:42,250 --> 00:30:43,610
<font color="#138ce9">MARY:</font> <i>Birmingham?</i>

599
00:30:43,610 --> 00:30:44,780
Hello?

600
00:30:44,780 --> 00:30:46,380
<font color="#138ce9">KAY:</font> <i>Hello, Ben.</i>

601
00:30:46,380 --> 00:30:47,680
Hello, Katharine.

602
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:50,650
<i>I'm sorry
to bother you so late.</i>

603
00:30:50,650 --> 00:30:53,990
<i>Listen, were you able to make
any headway with Mr. Sheehan?</i>

604
00:30:53,990 --> 00:30:56,820
<font color="#ff00ff">(GROANS)</font> No, no. I haven't.

605
00:30:56,830 --> 00:31:01,030
<i>I just had an odd conversation
with Bob McNamara...</i>

606
00:31:01,030 --> 00:31:05,470
<i>and I think</i> The Times <i>may
have a big story tomorrow.</i>

607
00:31:06,100 --> 00:31:07,830
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font> Oh, damn it.

608
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:10,670
<i>You know, he wouldn't
give me any details...</i>

609
00:31:10,670 --> 00:31:15,980
<i>but Bob said it was quite
detrimental to him and...</i>

610
00:31:37,570 --> 00:31:39,330
Ben!

611
00:31:39,340 --> 00:31:41,000
- We got 'em.
- <font color="#ff00ff">(BEN SIGHS)</font>

612
00:31:41,010 --> 00:31:42,600
We got 'em.

613
00:31:42,610 --> 00:31:43,640
Huh?

614
00:31:43,640 --> 00:31:45,310
- Yeah, quite good.
- The happy couple.

615
00:31:45,310 --> 00:31:47,280
- Hey, chief!
- Mr. Bradlee.

616
00:31:47,280 --> 00:31:49,440
So, did you
track down Sheehan?

617
00:31:49,450 --> 00:31:53,320
No, but, I saw a mock-up
of tomorrow's front page.

618
00:31:53,980 --> 00:31:55,950
There's a big gap.

619
00:31:55,950 --> 00:31:57,690
Nothing there but the name.

620
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,220
Shit.

621
00:32:03,230 --> 00:32:04,600
Shit.

622
00:32:05,060 --> 00:32:06,430
Shit!

623
00:32:14,270 --> 00:32:16,270
- Give us three.
- Here you go.

