00:32:16,270 --> 00:32:18,810
Here, here, here.
Thank you, thank you.

625
00:32:19,380 --> 00:32:20,840
Thanks, got it.

626
00:32:26,780 --> 00:32:28,520
<font color="#138ce9">FEMALE OPERATOR:</font> <i>General Haig, sir.</i>

627
00:32:28,520 --> 00:32:29,820
- <font color="#138ce9">NIXON:</font> <i>Hi, Al.</i>
-<font color="#138ce9"> HAIG:</font> <i>Yes, sir.</i>

628
00:32:29,820 --> 00:32:31,990
<font color="#138ce9">NIXON:</font> <i>What about
the casualties last week?</i>

629
00:32:31,990 --> 00:32:33,220
<i>You got that figure yet?</i>

630
00:32:33,220 --> 00:32:35,890
<font color="#138ce9">HAIG:</font> <i>No, sir, but I think
it's gonna be quite low.</i>

631
00:32:36,290 --> 00:32:37,530
<font color="#138ce9">NIXON:</font> <i>Fine.</i>

632
00:32:37,530 --> 00:32:40,390
<i>Okay. Nothing else of interest
in the world today?</i>

633
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:42,900
<font color="#138ce9">HAIG:</font> <i>Yes, sir.
Very significant...</i>

634
00:32:42,900 --> 00:32:46,330
<i>this goddamn</i>
New York Times <i>expose...</i>

635
00:32:46,340 --> 00:32:48,130
<i>...of the most
highly classified</i>

636
00:32:48,140 --> 00:32:49,840
<i>documents of the war.</i>

637
00:32:49,840 --> 00:32:52,070
<font color="#138ce9">NIXON:</font> <i>You mean that was
leaked out of the Pentagon?</i>

638
00:32:52,080 --> 00:32:56,410
<font color="#138ce9">HAIG:</font> <i>The whole study that
was done for McNamara.</i>

639
00:32:56,410 --> 00:33:00,650
<i>This is a devastating, uh,
security breach...</i>

640
00:33:00,650 --> 00:33:03,120
<i>of the greatest magnitude
of anything I've ever seen.</i>

641
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:05,390
<font color="#138ce9">NIXON:</font> <i>Well, what's being
done about it then?</i>

642
00:33:05,390 --> 00:33:07,150
<i>Did we know
this was coming out?</i>

643
00:33:07,160 --> 00:33:08,760
<font color="#138ce9">HAIG:</font> <i>No, we did not, sir.</i>

644
00:33:08,760 --> 00:33:10,190
<font color="#138ce9">FEMALE OPERATOR:</font> <i>I have Doctor Kissinger.</i>

645
00:33:10,190 --> 00:33:12,960
<font color="#138ce9">NIXON:</font> <i>Henry, the thing to me
is just unconscionable.</i>

646
00:33:12,960 --> 00:33:15,160
<i>This is treasonable action
on the part</i>

647
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:17,430
<i>of the bastards
that put it out.</i>

648
00:33:17,430 --> 00:33:19,130
<font color="#138ce9">KISSINGER:</font> <i>I'm absolutely certain...</i>

649
00:33:19,140 --> 00:33:22,900
<i>that this violates
all sorts of security laws.</i>

650
00:33:22,910 --> 00:33:24,600
<font color="#138ce9">NIXON:</font> <i>People have gotta
be put to the torch</i>

651
00:33:24,610 --> 00:33:26,580
<i>for this sort of thing.</i>

652
00:33:27,880 --> 00:33:31,550
Christ! McNamara knew
we couldn't win in '65.

653
00:33:31,550 --> 00:33:34,450
That's six goddamn years ago.

654
00:33:37,290 --> 00:33:38,760
Well, at least
we got the wedding.

655
00:33:41,590 --> 00:33:43,520
Is anybody else tired
of reading the news

656
00:33:43,530 --> 00:33:45,930
instead of reporting it?

657
00:33:45,930 --> 00:33:47,090
Do we have any leads?

658
00:33:47,100 --> 00:33:48,530
There's a guy Phil and I know
in Boston...

659
00:33:48,530 --> 00:33:49,630
who worked at Defense

660
00:33:49,630 --> 00:33:50,970
when McNamara
commissioned the study.

661
00:33:50,970 --> 00:33:52,530
All right, call him.

662
00:33:52,540 --> 00:33:54,400
Anybody else?

663
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:56,540
So that's it?

664
00:33:56,540 --> 00:33:59,510
Our best goddamn lead
is coming from editorial?

665
00:33:59,510 --> 00:34:01,310
<font color="#ff00ff">(SCOFFS)</font>
Well, we are sucking hind tit

666
00:34:01,310 --> 00:34:02,580
in our own backyard.

667
00:34:02,580 --> 00:34:04,510
Ben, come on,
it's one story.

668
00:34:04,510 --> 00:34:06,450
No, it's 7,000 pages...

669
00:34:06,450 --> 00:34:08,550
detailing how
the White House has been

670
00:34:08,550 --> 00:34:10,650
lying about the Vietnam War
for 30 years.

671
00:34:10,650 --> 00:34:15,960
It's Truman and Eisenhower
and Jack and LBJ lying.

672
00:34:15,960 --> 00:34:18,260
Lying about Vietnam.

673
00:34:18,260 --> 00:34:20,160
And you think
that's one story?

674
00:34:21,330 --> 00:34:23,100
Let's do our jobs.

675
00:34:24,500 --> 00:34:26,040
Find those pages!

676
00:34:30,770 --> 00:34:32,370
Ben, uh...

677
00:34:32,380 --> 00:34:34,940
I might have something.
Maybe.

678
00:34:34,940 --> 00:34:37,980
Well, let me know when it's
a little less wishy-washy.

679
00:34:37,980 --> 00:34:41,190
I'm gonna go chase down
a lead of my own.

680
00:34:45,190 --> 00:34:48,220
<font color="#138ce9">KAY:</font> Why don't you cut
your bangs, just a little bit?

681
00:34:48,230 --> 00:34:49,960
Mummy,
I'm right in the middle.

682
00:34:50,430 --> 00:34:51,860
<font color="#ff00ff">(KAY SIGHS)</font>

683
00:34:55,670 --> 00:34:58,430
It's a bit hard to read,
